#: ../../K/KIBO.rst:10
msgid ""
"[acronym] Knowledge In, Bullshit Out. A summary of what happens whenever "
"valid data is passed through an organization (or person) that deliberately "
"or accidentally disregards or ignores its significance. Consider, for "
"example, what an advertising campaign can do with a product's actual "
"specifications. Compare :ref:`GIGO`\\; see also :ref:`SNAFU-principle`\\."
msgstr ""
"[頭字語]Knowledge In, Bullshit "
"Out(ゴミを入れればゴミが出る)。有効なデータが、意図的にせよ偶然にせよその意義を無視ないし軽視する組織(あるいは人)を通過したときに起こることを要約したもの。たとえば、広告キャンペーンが製品の実際の仕様に対して何をしうるかを考えてみるとよい。\\"
" :ref:`GIGO`\\ と比較。\\ :ref:`SNAFU-principle`\\ も参照。"

#: ../../K/KIBO.rst:16
msgid ""
"James Parry <kibo@world.std.com>, a Usenetter infamous for various "
"surrealist net.pranks and an uncanny, machine-assisted knack for joining any"
" thread in which his nom de guerre is mentioned. He has a website at "
"`http://www.kibo.com/ <http://www.kibo.com/>`_."
msgstr ""
"James Parry "
"<kibo@world.std.com>。さまざまなシュルレアリスム的なネットいたずらと、自分の通り名が言及されたあらゆるスレッドに加わる、機械の助けを借りた不気味なまでの能力で悪名高いUsenet利用者。彼のウェブサイトは\\"
" `http://www.kibo.com/ <http://www.kibo.com/>`_\\ にある。"
